    missionQuote: "“Go into all the world and share the Gospel. Go teach all nations.”",
    leadershipEyebrow: "LEADERSHIP",
    leadershipTitle: "People who serve with purpose.",
    leadershipLead: "Meet the dedicated people who faithfully serve alongside Sparrows Gate Mission. Through compassion, prayer, and practical support, they help share the love of Jesus with children and families in the communities we serve.",
    leaderRole1: "Founders",
    leaderName1: "DEAN and ALBA TINNEY",
    leaderQuoteIntro1: "Words from Dean and Alba.",
    leaderQuote1: "Our goal at Sparrows Gate Mission is that homeless children and single, destitute moms and their children in Mexico, Belize, the Amazon and the Philippines will come to know, love and serve Jesus. James 1:27 says that true religion is caring for orphans and widows, and for more than 40 years we have done our best to love and care for them through schools, orphanages and homes for single, destitute moms and their children. The words of Psalm 67:2 are a constant reminder of our passionate plea: “Send us around the world with the news of your saving power and your eternal plan for all mankind.” Most people think that the poorest child is the one without food, shelter, clothing or limbs; but the poorest child is the one without hope and without love. Knowing that a destitute, unloved child is waiting for someone to share the love of Jesus is reason enough for us to GO to the regions beyond.",
    leaderRole2: "Leadership Member",
    leaderName2: "Leader Name Two",
    leaderBio2: "Chris Davis is Executive Administrator of Sparrows Gate. His years of business experience as a district manager of a Procter & Gamble subsidiary are a great benefit to Sparrows Gate. Over the years, he has brought many youth groups to Sparrows Gate in Mexico to help with ministry, projects and building efforts. Mission founder Dean Tinney consults with Mr. Davis on many issues related to operations in Mexico, Belize and the Philippines.",
    leaderQuoteIntro2: "Words from Chris Davis.",
    leaderQuote2: "“For many years now I have been bringing youth groups from Salem, Oregon, to serve the poor children of Baja at Sparrows Gate Mission’s children’s home and schools. We go to give but always come back with more than we gave. The verse, ‘Give and it shall be given unto you,’ comes to mind. Our young people agree. Giving our time and talent—and even a cup of cold water—to poor children is rewarding beyond belief.”",
    leaderRole3: "Leadership Member",
    leaderName3: "Leader Name Three",
    leaderQuoteIntro3: "Words from Bobbi Lucas.",
    leaderQuote3: "“My husband and I met Dean and Alba almost 40 years ago at a church in San Diego. Soon after that meeting, we began going down to support their mission in Tijuana and then in Las Palmas. They have never wavered in their mission of helping, feeding and educating as many poor children as possible. Sparrows Gate is exemplary when it comes to doing just that. Dean and Alba Tinney have the faith and integrity to follow through and see children—and even families—succeed. They focus on excellence in every way. This is why being asked to be a board member was not a difficult decision for me.”",
    leaderBio4: "Maria’s ministry experience includes a lifetime of service in outreach and discipleship. She has provided counseling and support to individuals and families in communities surrounding the church, served in hotel ministry, coordinated volunteer groups for hot breakfasts and weekend worship services, participated in mission trips to Tijuana orphanages, ministered to youth in correctional facilities, and supported homeless-shelter outreach in Los Angeles. Maria is also actively involved in children’s and youth ministry and teaches Sunday school classes from kindergarten through high school.",
    leaderQuoteIntro4: "Words from Maria Montes.",
    leaderQuote4: "“I’m honored to have accepted a position as a board member of Sparrows Gate. I truly believe in its mission to reach children for God’s kingdom. It reflects God’s heart that children come to know God early in life so they can flourish and be enriched through the knowledge and love of Christ. In turn, they will bring others and draw them to our Abba Father.”",
    leaderBio5: "Lee’s walk with the Lord began in 1971 when he was 23. He has been married for 52 years and has two children and three granddaughters. Lee taught high school math and counseled in public and private schools for 39 years. His missions experience includes many short-term trips to Mexico, Venezuela and the Philippines. He also served full time with Campus Crusade in Thailand for four years.",
    leaderQuoteIntro5: "Words from Lee Wadell.",
    leaderQuote5: "“I have been involved with Sparrow’s Gate ministries since the late 1980s, when Dean and Alba began a small children’s home outside of Tijuana at a former pig farm. Since then I have continued to pray and support the work as much as possible. Over the years, the time and circumstances were never right for me to join the board, but now I think it is a good time to serve as a board member.”",
    leaderBio6: "Keith began a relationship with Jesus in July 1973 while serving in the USMC. Keith and Leilani have been married since January 1974. They have three sons, three daughters-in-law and seven grandchildren who all follow the Lord. Keith spent his working years in the swimming-pool business—servicing, repairing and building—and his son took over the business in 2021.",
    leaderQuoteIntro6: "Words from Keith Cowell.",
    leaderQuote6: "“It has been a pleasure and a learning experience to watch God at work in Dean and Alba over the years. They have never lost their exuberance or desire to serve young people in Mexico, Belize, the Philippines and South America. I feel honored to be a part of the Missions Board for Sparrows Gate and, as God directs, will do what I can to be of service to Sparrows Gate.”",
